24/06/2007
SREBRENICA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The chief of the EU police mission, Brigadier General Vincenzo Coppola, said on Friday (June 22nd) that the security situation in Srebrenica is satisfactory and that he expects a ceremony marking the 12thn anniversary of the Srebrenica massacre on July 11th to pass without incident.
Coppola's statement followed a meeting with Republika Srpska police head Uros Pena and Srebrenica Mayor Abdurahman Malkic to discuss security arrangements for the event.
A crowd of 25,000 people is expected.
(Nezavisne Novine - 23/06/07;
EUPM website, RTRS - 22/06/07)
